1. Why, for Nietzsche, is “deception” at the heart of language and cognition?
2. What would Nietzsche say about the relationship between a) the mental picture or concept we have of “rock,” b) the word “rock,” and c) an actual rock, in and of itself?
3. On p. 768, N asks himself, “What, then, is truth”?  What is his answer?
4. Why is the human “an architectural genius”?  What does this imply about the capacity of language to build something new, as opposed to its capacity to describe?
5. What are the two types of humanity that Nietzsche describes at the end of the essay?
6. How would you describe N’s style?  How does his style as a writer relate to the content of his essay?
